Évaluation publiée le 28 décembre 2023
Cloud Climbers offers a surreal and captivating first-person walking simulation that delves into the poignant theme of humanity's struggle and the end of civilization. Players are invited to explore breathtaking sky-bound ruins, unraveling the mysteries behind their creation and the profound significance they hold.

Despite its brevity, the game manages to convey a deeply meaningful narrative within a short time frame, making it a standout experience. The themes of desperation, shortsightedness, greed, love, and even miracles are thoughtfully woven into the storytelling, providing players with multiple angles to contemplate within the span of 10-20 minutes.

What's truly remarkable about Cloud Climbers is that, despite being a free title, it stands shoulder to shoulder with many paid games in terms of quality and impact. Its ability to engage players and provoke introspection while maintaining a concise and accessible format is commendable.

For those who appreciate walking simulations or are simply curious to explore a unique and evocative narrative, Cloud Climbers is a must-play. Its brevity and no-cost nature make it an accessible and risk-free venture, ensuring that anyone can delve into its thought-provoking world without hesitation.

Overall, Cloud Climbers is a standout title that deserves attention and acclaim for its ability to deliver a deeply moving experience within a short and free package. It's a testament to the fact that quality storytelling and impactful gameplay can be found in unexpected places, and it's an experience that shouldn't be missed.

Évaluation publiée le 22 octobre 2023
Der vierte Turm ist einfach der beste!

Cloud Climber ist ein kleiner storybasierter Walking Simulator. Hier geht es um eine Welt in der Regen nicht mehr vorkommt und demnach nach den Wolken versucht wird zu greifen. Wie das alles ausgeht, findet ihr am besten selbst raus.

Grafisch ist das Spiel in einer sehr hübschen Cell-Shading Optik. Diese passt sehr zu dem apokalyptischen Feeling, welches hier aufkommen soll. Zudem ist der Protagonist sehr gut vertont, allerdings nur auf englisch.

Ich mach es hier kurz: Wer eine kleine aber feine Story erzählt bekommen will, der kann sich dieses Spiel auf jeden Fall anschauen. Wer Action oder schwierige Rätsel sucht, der wird hier allerdings nicht fündig.

Évaluation publiée le 4 octobre 2023
EN + GER

EN
Cloud Climber is a very very short as well as interesting game. Interesting because it's through diary
entries creates a world that leaves you thinking. The artistic realization of the idea "What would happen if humanity ran out of water?" was fascinating.
Feel free to try the game... it's available for free on Steam.

GER
Cloud Climber ist ein sehr sehr kurzes als auch interessantes Spiel. Interessant deshalb, weil es durch Tagebucheinträge eine Welt entstehen lässt, die einen nachdenklich zurücklässt. Die künstlerische Umsetzung des Gedankens "Was würde passieren, wenn der Menschheit das Wasser ausgehen würde?" war faszinierend.
Probiert das Game ruhig aus... es ist kostenlos auf Steam erhältlich.

Recommandé
0.3 h en tout
Évaluation publiée le 1 octobre 2023
This quite the somber game. It shows us the struggles of life all of us go through... the desperation, the frustration, and even the despair... but also showing us the light at the end of the tunnel and life's surprises when you least expect it. It shows us Hope.

The Narrator's voice is very calm and soothing, almost as if you know this person from childhood, which added another layer of emotion for me. This game has sort of rustic beauty to it... I can't really explain it in words other than to say try out this game. It really gave me an emotional roller-coaster. It certainly left me yearning for more... made me wish this to be developed into a full-fledged game. It's beautiful in a melancholic way...

Have a go at this game. It's free after all. You won't regret it.

如果沉浸式的去玩，你将会得到体验不错的十五分钟

玩法主要是探索，需要找一些道具。难度很低甚至不算解密。背景故事一方面是主角口述，另一方面是偷看别人的日记（？
景色很好。物品纹理是手绘风格的，很有特色。想要运行最高画质还是要一定配置的也可能是我电脑太烂
还有，主角配音真的太苏了！

唯一的问题是只有英文，不过不很难，顶多初中水平就能看懂大意。
大概是：为了躲避沙尘暴，人们决定建高塔。主角就是建塔的一员。但是地面上发生了暴乱，有人把他们的水源抢了，上面的人打不到水。最后只剩下主角。主角决定去另一个高塔，不确定要干什么。游戏过程就是绕到塔上。到了之后就是感慨美景。然后最后天上下起雨，可能是什么暗示吧。

1.7 h en tout
Évaluation publiée le 24 juillet 2023
"Cloud Climber" is a surreal first person walking sim about the end of humanity. You will explore magnificent sky-bound ruins and you will also learn why they were built. This game has an interesting plot, hand-drawn graphics, a detailed environment and a voiced narration.
It's a short game as it took me only 10 minutes to finish it. It has only one ending and there isn't a save feature, so you will need to complete the game in a single sitting. I would give it a 1/10 difficulty rating as the gameplay is minimal and the instructions are pretty clear during the whole game (you need to explore the magnificent sky-bound ruins).
Cloud Climber is a short narrative adventure game where you must explore each tower to uncover the full story of what happened. You need to find a way to the last tower and continue building the tower until you reach the clouds. The game is a casual thought provoking experience, that tells a unique and compelling story.
After everyone has met their end, the main character begins his adventure to the 4th tower, the tallest of the 4 towers featured in this game. You go along reading diaries and fixing the towers. I really enjoyed the atmosphere and the building tension. The ending touched me in a way that I feel would be too revealing of the rest of the game to include, however I found it to be suiting for the character and his outlook.
It's a game about humanity's desperate measures to survive, about their short sightedness and late reactions, about their greed, selfishness, and last but not least, about miracles. The hand-drawn graphics are amazing and the voiced narration is well adapted to the game.
All things considered, this game has a lot of potential and I will definitely try more games published by this developer. I would recommend this game to players that like surreal first person walking sim games or to the casual players that are trying new games/doing playthroughs.
If you want, you can check my full game playthrough here:
Vidéo YouTube™: Cloud Climber | Full Game Playthrough

Simple but it sticks in your head. And so many games and movies now are in some kind of lonely, post-apocalyptic setting, so it takes some work, however subtle, to do that. It's surprising to me that most of this developer's games are horror, because this totally sparks my interest to play another exploratory game from them!

If you want a short and boredom killing game, or if you just are looking through the free games (Like me) this is pretty good. 7/10

The game kind of reminds me of the story of The Tower Of Babylon from the Bible. One day, everyone on Earth decided to combine their forces and build a tower to 'reach the heavens'. God saw this as a problem, so he confused the peoples' language. Because no one understood anyone anymore, they all stopped working and dispersed.

Personne n'a trouvé cette évaluation utile

Recommandé
0.2 h en tout
Évaluation publiée le 9 avril 2023
Cloud Climber is a very short walking simulator that is set in a post-apocalyptic world where dust storms have made it impossible for people to live on the surface of the earth. To survive and find water people started building taller and taller towers to try to get up above the clouds.
It's effective in building a desolate atmosphere and the art style is really nice. The textures have a gorgeous hand-drawn aestetic and overall the presentation is striking.
There's not much to the story though, which is perhaps to be expected when the game is only about 10-15 minutes long, but I feel they could have done more with the premise. It doesn't help that the notes that you read feel arbitrary and unrealistic.

Personne n'a trouvé cette évaluation utile
0
Recommandé
0.2 h en tout
Évaluation publiée le 23 mars 2023
So I completed this game 2 months back and came here to write a review on Cloud Climber.
Graphics - Beautiful hand drawn graphics
Now lets talk about the real deal,
Gameplay - It's a really short game, I completed this in 15 mins as you can see by my game time. It's not much except walking and repairing some bridges and stairs. There are a few letters/diaries you come across while walking. That's it.

Story - There is not much to it. I would not give any spoilers here but you can get a rough idea of it by reading the description. The notes(diary written by different people) that you find while walking are connected to each other and the writing and voice acting is really well done. The story is like a short story in form of a video game

Final verdict - definitely check it out if you are into indie games and are looking for a game that can be completed in half an hour session, it is free afterall. Hope you all have a good day.

Well , I'll admit , when a game is this short is it really worth considering it a play through in its own right? I'm not sure. But as for what the game does do , it's a potent story told in diary entries about a world on the edge of extinction as the water of the world has all but dried up. In search of a saviour they take to the skies , hoping one day rain might come again , and save them. Which is how this 15 minute journey ends. An atmospheric walking simulator with expertly hand drawn details.

I liked it. 7/10.

Cloud Climber

Positives:
+ Nice voiceacting/storytelling
+ Acceptable handdrawn graphics
+ Ok made towers
+ Good sound
+ Its free

Negatives:
- No voiceover on the letters
- Not much to see or do
- Slow walking speed and no run function
- Head-bob that cant be disabled
- Very short (over in 15 minutes)

Total Score: 5/10

Évaluation publiée le 4 janvier 2023
Muy buena historia, reflexiva y relajadora e inquietante al mismo tiempo.

Los gráficos están geniales, me gustaría un juego ♥♥♥ este motor y diseño.

Como observación general, u overview, me quedaría ♥♥♥ las reseñas de Emil Holub y Morhaugn

Emil Holub a écrit :
This isn't really a game. Heck, it's barely even a demo... there are longer-lasting demos. I played for a full 36 minutes and about half of that was spent alt-tabbed out to Windows. Veeeeeery very short walking sim.

PROS:
- That being said, in terms of game mechanics it has no real flaws, although as-is there isn't enough there to cause flaws.
- And the graphics style is pretty nice. I like the sort of Bendy style of the look.
- I also enjoyed the story-building, such as it was. It's impressive that in such a short experience the dev is able to thread together the start of a pretty solid-feeling story.

♥♥♥♥:
- Again... not much here. I mean you could seriously finish this in 5 minutes if you ignored the story notes, and probably less than that if you know exactly where the super small handful of items you need to pick up are at. Free though, ehh. Not the biggest ♥♥♥ ever.
- The narration bothered me. Someone in the protagonist's position wouldn't sound like this, like he's just sort of halfheartedly musing over his ultimate demise that he sees coming after realizing that he's the only one left - I would expect this level of concern over whether he'll have the hamburger or the hotdog for lunch today, not over your life ending. If this were to turn into something bigger, they'd probably want to do something about that. I realize this may just be a solo project though.
- But to dovetail off that last thought, this was clearly meant to end with the ending provided, so it wasn't a demo for things to come, no cliffhangers or 'to be continued' expectations here. Which I do see as a flaw, since this feels like it could be something a lot cooler if more effort were put towards it.
- Lastly, while not sure if this is my fault or the game's fault, somehow this title managed to drag my 3080ti, framelocked at 120fps, all the way up to almost 75c. It certainly added to the ambiance of being up on a tower in the sky, because my computer sounded like the wind. As there is no way to change anything in the settings related to graphics - any changes must be done from your graphics card GUI app, other than just setting general quality, which doesn't actually change anything in-game - I'm moreso blaming the programming for this one.

So while I won't say this is a good "game," I will say that this is a great practice run or tech demo, hopefully with takeaway improvements for future titles from this dev.

UPDATE: Ahh, well this explains quite a bit: "Cloud Climber is a short story based game that I made in one week for the 2020 Epic MegaJam, which took place in December."

Ok one week is pretty nuts!

Morhaugn a écrit :
A carefuly crafted short metaphorical wakling sim that makes you stop and evaluate your life and what you've acomplished. And I guess we all know we should do it from time to time, it is great to have someone remind us. Beautiful and thank you for your work <3

Évaluation publiée le 24 décembre 2022
Produit reçu gratuitement

花了大概半小时游玩了这款游戏，观感体验都还不错。
如题《攀云者》，这是一个关于在末世建造通天巴别塔的故事
游戏类型是我很少玩的第一人称步行模拟，可互动的东西蛮少的，你只能触碰门、读信和一些谜题（如果可以称作解密的话）附近的小工具，整体来说，更偏向叙事向。
故事的话，涉及剧透就隐藏了
一百年前世界气候发生了点小变故，天空不再有雨水落下，主角祖父母很有远见开始修建高塔，却被其他人嘲笑
“疯子，傻瓜……”伴随着如此难听的话语，祖父母向着云端攀爬。直到河流湖泊真的开始干涸，人们才大为失色，开始崇拜祖父母的远见，这一切也只是持续到高塔蓝图被偷而已。很快，周围有很多高塔林立而起，不过，末日并没有消除人们的隔阂，每座高塔都离得相当远。人们拼尽一切渴求生存，但努力似乎都已经化为云烟。
主角像是从破旧被褥醒来，怀着平静的心情，揣着一杯，走过一座座高塔，如同虔诚的巡礼者。
“真美丽啊，如此平静”主角看着前人的努力与血汗凝结成的奇迹，不由自主的感叹
“所有人都已经离去，如今只剩我一个人……劳累了这么久，也该休息了……”
在最后一座塔顶，主角环视云顶之下这些高塔废墟，就在要探身跃出结束自己劳累的一生的时候，他听见了这辈子从未耳闻的，只存在长辈言语故事中的轰隆雷鸣声，瓢泼大雨降落在身上，犹如神迹……
游戏结束
氛围很到位，画面美术也很不错，看着高塔之下无边的雾霾和沙尘，铺陈整片天空的云雾，让人有种喘不过气的窒息感，不仅如此，每座塔的起始位置都没法往下，仔细看的话所有的楼梯似乎都已经拆掉了，这是已经失去了回到地面的希望才会将下楼的台阶拆掉，只为孤注一掷直奔星辰云海……
这些岌岌可危的通天巴别塔，让人……无声叹息……
